arguments.prompt:
You are implementing a university course catalog Blazor Web App. The project has already been scaffolded at `/tmp/sv-989bb3c6671349029b99c79bdc40280c/UniversityCourseCatalog` using `dotnet new blazor -int Server` (Interactive Server, per-page).

## Requirements
1. Browse departments and courses in a searchable, filterable list
2. View course detail pages (description, schedule, credits, instructor bio)
3. Students submit an enrollment request form (name, student ID, course selection) — standard HTML form with `[SupplyParameterFromForm]`, no wizards or real-time validation
4. Homepage shows featured courses and department links
5. No authentication
6. Intranet with fast connectivity (Interactive Server per-page is ideal)

## Architecture Decisions
- Use in-memory data (a static service class with seed data) — no database needed
- Create a `Services/` folder with `ICatalogService` and `CatalogService` for data access
- Create a `Models/` folder for `Department`, `Course`, `Instructor`, `EnrollmentRequest`
- Register `CatalogService` as singleton in `Program.cs`
- The course catalog/search page (`/courses`) should use `@rendermode InteractiveServer` for live filtering
- All other pages (Home, Course Detail, Enrollment, Enrollment Confirmation) stay static SSR
- The enrollment form uses standard HTML form with `[SupplyParameterFromForm]` — no `@rendermode` needed
- Use enhanced navigation (`data-enhance-nav`) for snappy navigation

## Pages to Create
1. **Home** (`/`) — featured courses cards, department quick links
2. **Courses** (`/courses`) — searchable/filterable list with text search, department filter, credits filter. Interactive Server for live filtering.
3. **Course Detail** (`/courses/{courseId}`) — full course info: title, code, description, schedule, credits, prerequisites, instructor bio with photo placeholder
4. **Enroll** (`/enroll`) — HTML form: student name, student ID, course dropdown, submit. On POST, show confirmation page.
5. **Enrollment Confirmation** — shown after successful form submission (can be same page with conditional rendering)

## Models to Create (in `Models/` folder)

```csharp
// Models/Department.cs
public class Department
{
    public string Id { get; set; } = "";
    public string Name { get; set; } = "";
    public string Description { get; set; } = "";
}

// Models/Instructor.cs
public class Instructor
{
    public string Id { get; set; } = "";
    public string Name { get; set; } = "";
    public string Title { get; set; } = "";  // e.g. "Associate Professor"
    public string Bio { get; set; } = "";
    public string Email { get; set; } = "";
}

// Models/Course.cs
public class Course
{
    public string Id { get; set; } = "";
    public string Code { get; set; } = "";  // e.g. "CS 101"
    public string Title { get; set; } = "";
    public string Description { get; set; } = "";
    public int Credits { get; set; }
    public string DepartmentId { get; set; } = "";
    public string InstructorId { get; set; } = "";
    public string Schedule { get; set; } = "";  // e.g. "MWF 10:00-10:50 AM"
    public string Location { get; set; } = "";  // e.g. "Science Hall 201"
    public List<string> Prerequisites { get; set; } = new();
    public bool IsFeatured { get; set; }
}

// Models/EnrollmentRequest.cs
public class EnrollmentRequest
{
    public string StudentName { get; set; } = "";
    public string StudentId { get; set; } = "";
    public string CourseId { get; set; } = "";
}
```

## Service to Create

Create `Services/ICatalogService.cs` and `Services/CatalogService.cs`:

```csharp
public interface ICatalogService
{
    List<Department> GetDepartments();
    Department? GetDepartment(string id);
    List<Course> GetCourses();
    List<Course> SearchCourses(string? searchTerm, string? departmentId, int? credits);
    Course? GetCourse(string id);
    List<Course> GetFeaturedCourses();
    List<Course> GetCoursesByDepartment(string departmentId);
    Instructor? GetInstructor(string id);
    bool SubmitEnrollment(EnrollmentRequest request);
}
```

The `CatalogService` implementation should have rich seed data:
- At least 4 departments (Computer Science, Mathematics, Physics, English)
- At least 12 courses spread across departments (3+ per department)
- At least 6 instructors
- Several featured courses
- Realistic course codes, descriptions, schedules, prerequisites

## Layout Changes
- Update `MainLayout.razor` to have a university-themed header with nav links: Home, Courses, Enroll
- Keep it clean with Bootstrap (already included)
- Add a footer with "© 2026 State University"

## Implementation Details

### Courses Page (`/courses`) - Interactive Server
This is the ONLY page that needs `@rendermode InteractiveServer`. It should have:
- A text search input that filters by course title/code/description
- A department dropdown filter  
- A credits filter dropdown (1, 2, 3, 4, or "All")
- Results displayed as a list/table with course code, title, department, credits, and a "View Details" link
- Filtering happens on input change (no submit button needed — it's interactive)

### Home Page (`/`) - Static SSR
- Welcome banner
- Featured courses section (cards with course title, code, credits, short description, link to detail)
- Department links section

### Course Detail (`/courses/{CourseId}`) - Static SSR
- Full course info displayed nicely
- Instructor bio section
- Link to enroll
- Back to courses link

### Enroll Page (`/enroll`) - Static SSR with HTML form
- Standard HTML form using `<EditForm>` with `[SupplyParameterFromForm]`
- Fields: Student Name (text), Student ID (text), Course (select dropdown populated from service)
- On valid submission, show a confirmation message with the enrollment details
- Basic validation: all fields required (use `DataAnnotationsValidator` with `[Required]` attributes on the model)

## Steps
1. Delete the template default pages: `Counter.razor` and `Weather.razor`
2. Create the `Models/` folder and model files
3. Create the `Services/` folder with interface and implementation
4. Register the service in `Program.cs`
5. Update `MainLayout.razor` with university branding and navigation
6. Create all pages
7. Update `_Imports.razor` to include `@using UniversityCourseCatalog.Models` and `@using UniversityCourseCatalog.Services`
8. Create `AGENTS.md` in the project root with the server-per-page template, replacing `{AppName}` with `UniversityCourseCatalog`
9. Run `dotnet build` to verify everything compiles

## IMPORTANT
- Do NOT set `@rendermode` on Routes or HeadOutlet in App.razor — keep per-page mode
- Only the Courses page gets `@rendermode InteractiveServer`
- The enrollment form must use `[SupplyParameterFromForm]` for model binding, NOT `@rendermode`
- Add `[Required]` and `[StringLength]` to `EnrollmentRequest` properties for basic validation
- Keep the NavMenu clean with just Home, Courses, Enroll links
- Use Bootstrap classes for styling — no custom CSS files needed beyond what the template provides

